This paper deals with learning representations invariant to common transformations of data, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a new approach to solving the Unlabeled Transformation Problem, which is a form of semi-supervised and one-shot learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper focuses on face recognition, which is a common application of computer vision, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) if the paper deals with facial recognition in the context of language processing. Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to the invariant kernel SVM, which is a common technique in the field of neural networks (cs.NE), suggesting that it may also belong to this sub-category.
